    "industrial_process_notes": "First synthesized by Eugen Baumann in 1872, but commercially impractical until Waldo Semon (B.F. Goodrich) developed plasticization techniques in 1926, enabling flexible PVC products by 1933 (e.g. with dibutyl phthalate). ~80% of global production uses suspension polymerization (particles ~100-180 micrometers), with emulsion (~12%) and bulk (~8%) polymerization making up the rest.",
